## Pi worker runtime metadata

The shared examples above use generic per-field `(source: ...)` annotations. For Pi, the
literal authoritative format is `audit_metadata`'s returned block: one `Agent-Harness: Pi
<version>` line followed by plain field lines with no per-field suffixes. Call it and paste
exactly what it returns, not the shared example's shape.

In an execution/worker session that authors a durable record, call `audit_metadata` once
before authoring it and paste its returned block verbatim. Never hand-write, guess, infer
from config or defaults, or use `unknown` for Model, Model-Provider, Session-ID, or Hostname;
`audit_metadata` is their only valid source.

`git commit` and `gh pr create` remain direct and un-intercepted: nothing attaches this block
or blocks publication if it is omitted. This is a manual, cooperative requirement.
